    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-05T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="475"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/64: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-05T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 5, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. The Junta<note n="2" xml:id="d475fn2">The Junta de Gobierno decreed its
                        establishment on June 4.</note> consists of <persName corresp="#p_PGA1"
                        >General Arturo Puga</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_DCG1">Carlos
                        Dávila</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MHE1">Eugenio Matte</persName>.
                    Last named has been for 2 years head of the Masonic Order. First named is
                    Minister of the Interior. <persName corresp="#p_GVCM1">Grove</persName> is
                    Minister of War. Other Ministers little known.</p>
                <p>Junta arrived at Moneda about 7 p.m. yesterday. <persName corresp="#p_GVCM1"
                        >Grove</persName> declared that they had support of the armed forces and
                    that they had come to replace <persName corresp="#p_MJE1">Montero</persName>’s
                    government by a socialist republic. <persName corresp="#p_MJE1"
                        >Montero</persName> called chief of the Santiago garrison who informed him
                    that the troops were not disposed to cooperate with the Government. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MJE1">Montero</persName> then said that nothing remained but for
                    him to retire. He did not resign and therefore remains constitutional President
                    of Chile.</p>
                <p>The Junta established itself by force, troops having occupied <pb facs="0536"
                        n="432" xml:id="pg_432"/> Moneda before the arrival of the revolutionists.
                    Junta states that it will respect the Constitution “insofar as it may be
                    compatible with the new order of things.”</p>
                <p>The declarations of the Junta have stunned and frightened the propertied classes.
                    The American executives are meeting with me at the Embassy this afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
